    &lt;Title&gt;Very poorly dad - treated with no care or dignity&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Julie&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Dad arrived from Preston on IV antibiotics with a view to going into care.
Dad fell within first 10 hours of being in Rookwood A - been in Preston Hospital for 10 weeks and did not fall once!
As a result he lost his confidence and within 24 hours had taken to his bed being given a bedpan and not encouraged or supported to get out to go to the toilet or sit in chair

Today he has become very poorly and when we asked for some dignity since he is not talking or eating, so could he go into a side room in case this is the end - were told none available
Asked for Bed/Bay manager to be contacted but apparently all bays in whole hospital are full.
So dad has no dignity no care or anything - sitting here with him in a ward with no care or help at all - lack of respect or care from the staff - no kindness shown at all to any of us at this difficult time&lt;/CommentText&gt;
